getLayerSource

public static ImageServer getLayerSource(String URL,
                                         String serviceName,
                                         String userName,
                                         String password,
                                         int cacheLimit)
                                  throws IOException
Deprecated. 
Creates a proxy for an ArcIMS ImageServer, and immediately calls refresh() to obtain the service info. Calling refresh() involves a round-trip to the ImageServer, and may take considerable time.

You can choose to cache or not cache images retrieved from the server by setting an appropriate value for the cacheLimit - a value of 0 == no caching

Parameters:
URL - a url of an ArcIMS site
serviceName - the name of an ArcIMS image service
userName - a user name to get access to a restricted ArcIMS service
password - a password to get access to a restricted ArcIMS service
cacheLimit - the cash limit
Returns:
the image server instance based on the ArcIMS image service proxy
Throws:
NullPointerException - if service is null
IllegalArgumentException - if service has null name, or if cacheLimit is less than 1
IOException - as a result of any errors detected within refresh()
See Also:
BaseImageLayerSource.BaseImageLayerSource(String,int)
